description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an Occupational Therapist within East Surrey Community Team for People with Learning Disabilities at Surrey and Border Partnership NHS Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is a Band 6 Occupational Therapist in East Surrey, 2 days (15hrs) per week, until mid-September 2021, to start as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly and dynamic Occupational Therapy team and Occupational Therapy is a valued member of our wider MDT. We serve the health needs for adults with Learning Disabilities in East Surrey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team bases are in Epsom and Redhill, though we are currently also working flexibly from home to a degree due to the current pandemic. The candidate must have a full and valid driving licence due to the community element of the role and the large geographical area that the East Surrey Community Team cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Occupational Therapy team comprises a Band 7, 6, 5 and an Occupational Therapist apprentice. This post is a short-term addition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This would suit an existing band 6 occupational therapist who would like to gain experience in working with people with learning disabilities or an experienced Band 5 looking for a challenge and experience at Band 6 level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate would be passionate about working with people with learning disabilities, have a grounded knowledge of occupational therapy, and be a self-directed motivated team player.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In practice we use the Model of Human Occupation to guide all our occupational therapy assessments and interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The occupational therapy leadership team is committed to an extensive, co-ordinated CPD programme including supervision, care group and trust wide trainings, core competence training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff are valued for their expertise in occupationally focussed interventions, and work as a core part of the multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information please contact Lindsey.mosley@sabp.nhs.uk 01737 288800&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to your application form!&lt;/p&gt;
